The paper deals with natural language processing and knowledge representation, which are topics commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of lambda calculus and the focus on logic programming suggest categories such as logic in computer science (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper also discusses complexity and completeness results, which are relevant to theoretical computer science (cs.LG).
